in a speech given at the opening day of the fourth seminar of the ruling burma socialist programme party ( bspp ) on 6 november 1969 , ne win formally rejected u nu 's proposal , saying that he took over power – and held on to it – not because he craved power but to uplift the welfare of the ' workers and peasants ' and that u nu 's proposals amounted to ' turning back the wheel ' .

